        "id": 3199603,
        "name": "SeanSydney",
        "username": "Sean_S_y_d_n_e_y",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/sean_s_y_d_n_e_y/{size}/3454_2.png",
        "created_at": "2021-07-18T23:57:52.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>This is so, so lovely!</p>\n<p>Flint and delicious waxy lemon oil on the nose, and more than anything an overwhelming sense of freshness and vitality. Seamlessly glides over the palate into a saline, somewhat nutty/yeasty finish. Doesn\u2019t show the heat of the vintage at all; it\u2019s not razor-sharp but still so energetic and alive. This is my second wine from these folks this year, and is just beautiful winemaking from great terroir.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 8,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-04T06:12:30.498Z",
